<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>An Australian live export ship has disappeared off the Japanese coast after being hit by a dangerous typhoon.</p>

<p>Two Australians, two New Zealanders along with 39 people from the Philippines are on board the vessel as well as 5,800 cattle. </p>

<p>The Japanese coast guard are now searching for the Gulf Livestock 1 that sent a distress signal after being hit by the typhoon in the East China Sea on Wednesday.</p>

<p>A lifeboat and a Filipino crew member were found drifting in the water on Wednesday night, the ABC reported.</p>

<p>The crew member had not sustained any life-threatening injuries. </p>

<p>The vessel had left New Zealand on August 14 and was due to arrive in China on Friday. </p>

<p>Rescue teams are continuing their search for the ship but are struggling against strong winds and rain from Typhoon Maysak. </p>

<p>More to come. </p>
